<h2>Best Time To Visit North East / Best Season to Visit North East</h2>
<p>November to April is considered the best time to visit North East. In this period, the North East completely turns to Diva and weather is suitable for all. If you&rsquo;re planning for North East then considering the best time to visit is really necessary, as the mountain region experiences frequent climate change.</p>

<h2>How to Reach North East / North East Travel Guide</h2>
<p>Getting into northeastern regions is super easy. You can choose a train, road trip, or flight to reach. Though some places might not have flight accessibility, in that case, you can take a train or reach the nearest airport and then take public transport to reach your destination.</p>

<h2>Best Places to Visit in North East / Top Tourist Places in North East</h2>

<h3>Sikkim</h3>
<p>Explore the elegance of mother nature in Sikkim, which holds unreal mountain beauty with evergreen surroundings. You can visit Kanchanjunga, Gangtok, and various monasteries. If you want to visit the beauty of Sikkim, then browse through our Sikkim tour packages and North East tour packages.</p>

<h3>Meghalaya</h3>
<p>The adobe of clouds has always been on the bucket list of many travelers for its mystic beauty. You can visit Shilong, Double Decker Bridge, and Cherrapunji, which are some of the top sightseeing places in Meghalaya. Book Meghalaya tour packages and North East tour packages to witness the spellbound beauty of these places.</p>

<h3>Assam</h3>
<p>Gateway of the North East, or tea basket of India; Assam is one of the best places to visit in the North East region. The rich diversity of the area has been a key attraction in Assam, which you can witness in Kaziranga National Park. Book North East travel packages with invisit.</p>

<h3>Manipur</h3>
<p>One of the best places to visit in north east, Manipur is a beautiful place to visit. This hidden jewel is rich in its culture and pure scenic beauty. You can visit Tamenglong, Imphal, Loktak Lake, and Sendra Island, which are the top sightseeing places in Manipur.</p>

<h3>Arunachal Pradesh</h3>
<p>The largest state among all the nort east states, Arunachal Pradesh is one of the top tourist places in north east. You can explore the temples, immerse yourself in the local culture, and enjoy the cuisine with our North East tour packages.</p>

<h3>Tripura</h3>
<p>Visit another beauty of the North East. Tripura is another best place to visit in the North East. Learn about its history and culture with invisit&rsquo;s Tripura tour packages and North East holiday packages.</p>


<h2>Top Things to do in North East / Best activities to do in North East</h2>


<h3>Visit Kaziranga National Park in Assam</h3>
<p>Kaziranga National park is one of the top things to do in north east. Explore the wide range of flora and fauna in Assam. Get north east tour packages at an affordable price only with invisit.</p>

<h3>Kayaking</h3>
<p>Kayaking is one of the top things to do on a north east tour. Float on the water surface and witness the beautiful surroundings along with it. While on north east trip don&rsquo;t miss out this best activities.</p>

<h3>Attend the Hornbill Festival</h3>
<p>If you&rsquo;re planning to visit Nagaland in December, you can witness the popular Hornbill festival in Kisama village in Assam. Enjoy the festival of light and energy with invisit&rsquo;s north east holiday packages.</p>

<h3>Waterfall Visits</h3>
<p>If you love watching waterfalls, the North East is a paradise for you. Spot magical waterfalls in every corner of north east and enjoy the serenity of these places.</p>

<h3>Witness the Largest River Island in the World</h3>
<p>Majuli is the largest river island in the world and is present in Assam. Explore Majuli and witness the beauty of the largest island, Majuli in Assam with our north east tour packages.</p>

<h3>Walk over the Living Root Bridge</h3>
<p>Walking over the living root bridge is one of the best activities to do in Meghalaya. Book Meghalaya tour packages and North East tour packages to explore the wonder of North East.</p>

<h3>Visit the Floating Lake</h3>
<p>Loktak, a floating lake in Manipur is one of the top things to do in North East. Book north east trip packages to witness the only floating lake in the world.</p>

<h3>Visit Mawsynram in Meghalaya</h3>
<p>Visiting Maswsynram in Meghalaya, an untouched settlement that is truly beautiful and a visual retreat to the eyes. Witness this mesmerizing place with our Meghalaya tour packages and north east tour packages.</p>

<h3>Visit Monastery</h3>
<p>North East holds lots of monasteries to visit and experience true serenity. You can explore Tibetan culture and history with our north east vacation packages.</p>

<h2>What to eat in the North East?</h2>

<h3>Masor Tenga</h3>
<p>A non-veg asami, fish curry recipe prepared with dried tomatoes gives it a unique tangy flavor. Masor Tenga is a must-try dish in the North East.</p>

<h3>Momos</h3>
<p>You can enjoy authentic momos of the north east with delicious chutney. Book north east tour packages with invisit to enjoy tasty momos of North East.</p>

<h3>Bamboo Fish</h3>
<p>A fish curry dish that is steamed in a bamboo shell. Perfectly steamed tender fish, served with chilli flakes and soup, is a must try dish in the North East.</p>

<h3>Jadoh</h3>
<p>While on a trip to north east, don't miss out on trying Jadoh, a famous local dish. You will definitely love this rice meat dish, which is loved by everyone.</p>

